Usage: get_op_cond [-help] <virtualOpcondName> {-library_file  | -P  | -V  | -T  }

-help                   # Prints out the command usage
<virtualOpcondName>     # Name of the operating condition to query
                        # (string, required)
-P                      # Returns the process value for the operating condition
                        # (bool, optional)
-T                      # Returns the temperature value for the operating
                        # condition (bool, optional)
-V                      # Returns the voltage value for the operating condition
                        # (bool, optional)
-library_file           # Name of library file (bool, optional)